                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#41r" facs="041">Fol. 41r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref>, attended by the angels <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#69r" facs="069">Fol. 69r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1002Annunciation">Annunciation</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#78v" facs="079">Fol. 78v</locus><desc>Three Ethiopian dignitaries</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#128v" facs="129">Fol. 128v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref>, raising Adam and Eve</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#160r" facs="160">Fol. 160r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> (in red ink and a crude hand) with caption <q>“Saint Michael, the archangel.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d6">
                    Decorative designs:
                    a line of alternating red and black dots serves as a section divider throughout (e.g., <locus target="#13v #14v #15r #15v" facs="014 015 016">folss. 13v, 14v, 15r, 15v, </locus>);
                    <locus target="#99r" facs="099">99r</locus> (line of black dots as major section divider)
                    </decoNote>
